<h3 id="ownership-and-permission">ownership and permission</h3>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nb">sudo chown</span> <span class="nt">-R</span> www-data:www-data /var/www/html
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>to allow the group www-data to take ownership of folder.</p>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nb">sudo </span>adduser username www-data
</code></pre></div></div>
<p>to add your user to the group www-data</p>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nb">sudo chmod</span> <span class="nt">-R</span> 775 /var/www/html/
</code></pre></div></div>
<p>To now change file permissions to 775 so that, (U)ser / owner can read, can write and can execute. (G)roup can read, can write and can execute. (O)thers can read, canâ€™t write and can execute.</p>

